1 appr opriations disbursement, OMES shall conduct a review of the
2 agency's budget to actuals to ensure the agency is staying within
3 budget constraints;
4 2. OMES shall provide a report to the Governor, the Speaker of
5 the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of
6 the Oklahoma State Senate, and the chairs and vice-chairs of the
7 standing committees of the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the
8 Oklahoma State Senate having primary responsibility for the
9 consideration of agency appropriations concerning the status of
10 revenue and expenditures of the agency;
11 3. The Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
12 Services shall be prohibited from entering into contracts that do
13 not clearly state a maximum fiscal obligation;
14 4. OMES shall review encumbrances for any multi-year purchase
15 orders or contracts to ensure that only the anticipated amount of
16 funds for the current fiscal year are encumbered; and
17 5. OMES shall prohibit the processing of payments for non-
18 budgeted expenditures.
19 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
